    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Help Doctors Who Help the Poor</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Victor Bloom letter calls for waiving of debt of doctors who work with the poor (July 30 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Cuts in Loan Program Squeeze Doctors Who Work With Poor'' (front page, July 30):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Cuts in Loan Program Squeeze Doctors Who Work With Poor'' (front page, July 30):</p>
        <p>If these doctors have been inadvertently shortchanged by the government, it should be easy enough to re-compensate them, merely by waiving their debt by the appropriate amount. Certainly one government agency can accommodate another in order to fulfill obligations honorably.</p>
        <p>VICTOR BLOOM, M.D.  Grosse Point, Mich., July 30, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a psychiatrist.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
